This document is a guide to set the problem of initialization of the wifi connection. Sometimes, the wpa_supplicant may have to be updated at each start up. Without the configuration below, you should at each startup of the raspberry, updating wpa_suppliant. In order to solve this issue, the following instructions may be your solution:

Step1: 
- Copy to /home/pi the file init_wlan0.py at https://github.com/AsmaBRZ/robot-explo/config_wlan/init_wlan0.py

Step2
To run the Python script at startup in raspberry you should open a terminal and follow the instructions below:
- Modify the file ".bashrc" with sudo nano /home/pi/.bashrc
- Add the following commands at the end of the file
	echo Running at boot 
	sudo python /home/pi/init_wlan0.py
- Save and close ".bashrc"
- On a terminal execute the command: reboot
Inspiration: https://www.dexterindustries.com/howto/run-a-program-on-your-raspberry-pi-at-startup/